  <notes>
    The PR description requirement from `bff-extensions.md` is non-negotiable. Even though this is a skeleton with no real logic, the checklist establishes the discipline for subsequent BFF additions. Treat the PR description as a deliverable, not an afterthought.

    The `AddJobProcessingModule` is the canonical reference. If your `AddActionEngineModule` doesn't look structurally identical (same naming, same options binding, same lifetime choices), revisit until it does.

    Do NOT register an impl for `IActionEngineFacade` in this task. That interface is created in parallel by task 015; its impl lands in a later phase. The DI registration of the facade impl is deferred â€” Phase 1 ships only the skeleton.

    Do NOT add NuGet packages. The skeleton uses only what's already in `Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj`. If you find yourself needing a package (e.g., Azure AI Search client), STOP â€” that's task 016's territory. Cross-task NuGet additions blow up the publish-size budget.

